1
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,160
Why clear them out?

2
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,280
This is great.

3
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:38,400
Young people are wonderful.

4
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,520
We're hosting this Four Treasures of the

5
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:42,520
Study Festival precisely for this buzz.

6
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,640
I just thought it looked messy.

7
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,160
I worried the officials might be annoyed.

8
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:51,960
Who changed this sign?

9
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:52,680
I did.

10
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,000
What do you think? Looks good, right?

11
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:55,720
Take it down.

12
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,080
Right now.

13
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,440
What are you up to?

14
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,360
Take it down immediately.

15
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,800
Secretary Peng.

16
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,920
The officials' car has arrived.

17
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,920
Come on, come on.

18
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,600
Come on, get moving, liven it up!

19
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:06,760
Quick, start dancing!

20
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,240
This way, sir.

21
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,120
Secretary Chen, Secretary Chen.

22
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,760
Hello, hello.

23
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,440
Hello.

24
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:18,920
Secretary Chen.

25
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:19,720
Secretary, hello, hello.

26
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:20,840
Welcome, welcome, welcome.

27
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,600
Let me introduce.

28
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,560
This is Secretary Peng of Taohua Town.

29
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,360
Secretary, I'm Peng Ruixue.

30
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:27,800
I know of you.

31
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,800
My daughter bought me some of

32
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:32,840
your Xuan paper notebooks for my office.

33
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,360
So we've also contributed to

34
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,560
Taohua Town's economy.

35
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,200
Thank you, honored officials.

36
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,800
With your care and support,

37
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,400
we'll surely do even better.

38
00:02:41,600 --> 00:02:42,280
Secretary.

39
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,200
I'm truly delighted by your visit.

40
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,600
Please come on stage and say a few words.

41
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,400
Yes, yes, yes.

42
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,560
Hello, sir.

43
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,160
I'm the deputy leader of this

44
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,400
Four Treasures of the Study Festival team.

45
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,400
My name is Luo Yuncheng.

46
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,560
Here's a speech I wrote just for you.

47
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,040
How about this,

48
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,720
have the lion dancers stop, would you?

49
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,680
The lions.

50
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,360
No, wait.

51
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,360
Hold on a moment.

52
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,200
Hold on a moment.

53
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,440
Take a break, everyone.

54
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,160
Alright.

55
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:06,640
Today,

56
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,200
let's not give speeches here.

57
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,200
Take a look around.

58
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,040
Lots of young people came today.

59
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:12,920
Let's not dampen their enthusiasm.

60
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,200
We're not here to give directives.

61
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,280
We're here to study and learn.

62
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,800
I have a suggestion.

63
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,480
Let's not

64
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,480
all cluster together as a big group.

65
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,200
We're visitors too, right?

66
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:23,920
Aren't we?

67
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,880
Let's split up and walk around individually.

68
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:27,400
Have a look.

69
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,600
Get a feel for it, okay?

70
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,000
Alright.

71
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:29,800
Whatever you say.

72
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:30,720
Let's do it this way then.

73
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,360
In half an hour,

74
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,800
we'll regroup right here.

75
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,840
Secretary Peng,

76
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,200
why don't you show us around first?

77
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:37,640
Sure.

78
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,200
Please, this way.

79
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:38,920
After you, everyone.

80
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:39,400
Let's go.

81
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,120
This way.

82
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,600
Not you.

83
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,880
The chief asked Secretary Peng to lead.

84
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:44,840
Same thing, same thing.

85
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,800
Today, visiting Taohua Town's

86
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,920
Four Treasures of the Study Festival,

87
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,120
I have many thoughts.

88
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,320
My first impression:

89
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,400
I never expected

90
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:58,360
such a large Four Treasures of the Study

91
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,960
Festival could be hosted by Taohua Town.

92
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,200
And done so well too.

93
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,800
I told Secretary Chen,

94
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,360
Secretary Peng and her Yang Women Generals

95
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,240
are remarkable.

96
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,320
Full of energy.

97
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:08,400
Of course,

98
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,800
behind them,

99
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:12,280
Jing County's departments have their backs.

100
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,200
On the way here,

101
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,880
Secretary Peng told me

102
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,200
this cultural festival

103
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,399
should turn a profit.

104
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,440
A government-led event

105
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:20,680
actually being profitable,

106
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,800
that's truly rare.

107
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,080
Of course,

108
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:25,280
I'm not encouraging our Party officials

109
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:27,040
to drop their work and go make money.

110
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,200
I want to talk about

111
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,960
my second deeper impression.

112
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:35,520
Why is this traditional cultural event,

113
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,920
which used to seem stale and outdated,

114
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,600
disconnected from the times,

115
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,280
now drawing so many young people

116
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,520
willing to get involved?

117
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:46,400
In planning, organizing, and coordinating

118
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,080
this cultural festival,

119
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,520
what did Taohua Town do right?

120
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,880
That's the purpose of our study today.

121
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:55,040
It's also why I suggested holding the meeting

122
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:58,960
at Sandy Field Rice Cafe.

123
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,480
I'm busy with work, so I rarely visit,

124
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:03,920
but I've always cared about Xuan paper heritage

125
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,720
and the industry's development.

126
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,400
I've learned that

127
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,360
Taohua Town didn't just host this

128
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,520
Four Treasures of the Study Festival well.

129
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:15,600
They've developed new Xuan paper wallpaper industries,

130
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,400
and blazed a new trail with Xuan paper cultural products.

131
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:22,600
From stagnation to flourishing prosperity.

132
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,120
I'm genuinely happy for all of you.

133
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,520
Government work must connect with the grassroots.

134
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,880
I've said this before,

135
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:31,760
outstanding traditional culture must also stay grounded.

136
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:34,960
Let the self-revival of traditional culture

137
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:38,200
deeply engage with the younger generation,

138
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,360
and further

139
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:42,200
resonate with this great era we live in.

140
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,880
Only then can we write

141
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,800
a new chapter of cultural confidence.

142
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:54,680
Lin Yiran

143
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,720
Come here.

144
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,240
Hello, everyone.

145
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,800
This young lady is

146
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,960
the Lin Yiran I mentioned to you.

147
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,360
Come over.

148
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,120
Hello, sir.

149
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,520
Oh, I know you.

150
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:06,680
You defied the town committee's decision,

151
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,520
so you dragged the town Party Secretary

152
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:10,120
to the county to file a complaint, right?

153
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,160
That's you, isn't it?

154
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,120
And you've got a nickname in town too,

155
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,280
Lin the Contrarian, right?

156
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:19,000
Only young people would stir up such a fuss.

157
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,720
But it also reflects that these young people

158
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,880
are pragmatic and truth-seeking,

159
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,200
bold in thought and action.

160
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,240
That's truly commendable.

161
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,560
Come, have a seat.

162
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,320
Come over.

163
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,560
Come on.

164
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:29,800
Come here.

165
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,920
Here, sit next to me.

166
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:31,600
Come on.

167
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,000
Here, Yiran, sit here.

168
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:37,440
Excuse me.

169
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:41,680
In contrast, some of our

170
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,800
cadres who love to pull rank

171
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,360
have failed to do this.

172
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,000
Hesitant and blindly following others,

173
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,560
they don't focus on work and development,

174
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,680
but obsess over their bosses' attitudes.

175
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:54,760
They'd rather do nothing

176
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:56,320
than risk doing something wrong.

177
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:59,120
This is typical lazy governance mentality.

178
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,240
I want to solemnly raise here

179
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,760
some suggestions about the bad tendencies

180
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,920
among our current leading cadres.

181
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,320
All day long, what they ponder

182
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,880
isn't how to serve the people,

183
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,520
but how to please their superiors.

184
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:17,200
They don't care about local development,

185
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:19,200
only their own political futures.

186
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,120
The people's eyes see clearly.

187
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,800
Such cadres will only be weeded out.

188
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,520
Our cadres must establish

189
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:29,320
a correct view of performance.

190
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:47,760
Did you hear?

191
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,680
Luo Yuncheng got an Intra-party warning.

192
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,440
Too light a punishment.

193
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,240
Not light at all.

194
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,760
Technically speaking,

195
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:57,880
he can't be promoted for a year.

196
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,680
But in reality, his political career

197
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,720
is basically over.

198
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,920
So you're finally a full Director now.

199
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,160
You should treat us.

200
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,080
Fine, I'll arrange time off for you right away.

201
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,720
Really?

202
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,320
No way.

203
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:10,360
I still have tons of work to do.

204
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,120
I'll work overtime.

205
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,560
Seriously?

206
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,760
How can you be so nice?

207
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,480
Let me tell you,

208
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,320
I'm so exhausted right now,

209
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,000
I just want to lie in bed for days.

210
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:19,560
Except for eating,

211
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,920
I don't want to do anything.

212
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,560
When you're truly exhausted,

213
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,360
you don't even want to eat.

214
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:25,920
Director,

215
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,720
you really want to work me to death.

216
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,440
Director Liao,

217
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,760
you've been working hard these days too.

218
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,240
Give yourself a day off.

219
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:33,960
Can't do it.

220
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,760
I've got a pile of things to do.

221
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,000
Who assigned you work?

222
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,400
I did, myself.

223
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,400
I need to post new short videos.

224
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,080
Yiran,

225
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,160
you probably don't know,

226
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,520
but our Director Liao right now

227
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,840
is absolutely killing it.

228
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,080
His videos get tens of thousands of likes.

229
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,800
Congratulations, Director Liao.

230
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:53,680
Don't be so quick to congratulate.

231
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,600
Director Liao's historical short videos

232
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,120
may get great like counts,

233
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,600
but the comment section

234
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,560
is basically a massive train wreck.

235
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,760
Netizens everywhere come to nitpick.

236
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:05,680
Director Liao,

237
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,080
why do they enjoy

238
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,440
listening to your nonsense so much?

239
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,680
Just for nitpicking and laughs.

240
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,200
They even gave Director Liao a nickname.

241
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,240
Triple Fail.

242
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,240
Historical facts, always fail.

243
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,880
Talking about the Four Treasures, always fail.

244
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,640
Ancient jokes and anecdotes, always fail.

245
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:20,840
What do you two know?

246
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,200
TV shows are about the plot,

247
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,680
but short videos are about emotion.

248
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:26,960
As long as the emotion hits,

249
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,680
viewers won't care about the details.

250
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,560
See?

251
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,760
Our Director Liao always has fresh tricks.

252
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,040
No, hold on.

253
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,680
I have to show you this video.

254
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,440
Which one?

255
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,000
This one.

256
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:46,000
Until the Tang Dynasty produced the painting sage Wu Daozi.

257
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,560
Everyone knows

258
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:51,160
"Wu's wind-blown drapery."

259
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:55,640
The ribbons on the clothes Wu Daozi painted

260
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:59,240
all seem to flutter in the wind.

261
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,760
Why?

262
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:05,120
Because he accidentally used Xuan paper.

263
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,840
Five shades of ink,

264
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,440
with layered, gradient effects.

265
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,000
Without Xuan paper,

266
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,440
every robe he painted would look like armor,

267
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,520
just a pitch-black blob.

268
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,120
From then on,

269
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:24,520
famous painters followed suit,

270
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:27,280
all using Xuan paper to paint.

271
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,000
And so,

272
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:32,360
not only did the ribbons flutter,

273
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:36,360
the clouds drifted, the mist drifted,

274
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,840
everything drifted.

275
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:43,440
That's the story of Wu Daozi and Xuan paper.

276
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,800
Follow Old Liao,

277
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,600
and I'll make you a person with substance.

278
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,720
Look at this comment. What does it say?

279
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,120
"Wu Daozi would rise from the grave hearing this."

280
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:54,960
And this one:

281
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,640
"Wu Daozi says he's taken the blame

282
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,880
for 1,300 years."

283
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,040
Director,

284
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:01,120
see for yourself.

285
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,640
Someone said you should apply for the Tang Dynasty Fiction Award.

286
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:05,720
Director Liao,

287
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,520
you really know how to spin a tale.

